Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Poor hematologic, renal, or hepatic function

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

outcome_measures.analysis_method: A descriptive summary of all toxicities will be reported.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of toxicities of simvastatin, topotecan hydrochloride, and cyclophosphamide, using the National Cancer Institute Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events version 4.0
outcome_measures.time_frame: Up to 30 days after the last dose of the investigational agent

outcome_measures.measure: Description of patterns of treatment, therapies, and clinical management
outcome_measures.time_frame: Approximately every 3-6 months through end of study, up to at least 36 months

outcome_measures.analysis_method: A repeated measures change-point model consisting of a decreasing and an increasing segment to estimate the distribution of the nadir time, using a prior uniform on the 24-month post-treatment period. Linear segments will be used unless initial analysis of the data suggests a nonlinear model. Quality of life will be compared with patient data listed in UMC 2-21.
outcome_measures.measure: Quality of life using the Neck Dissection Impairment Index questionnaire
